KF, 20 ΞΌg/ml leupeptin, 20 ΞΌg/ml benzamidine, 10 ΞΌg/ml pepstatin A, 40 ΞΌg/ml aprotinin, 1 mM PMSF, and 0.5% Tween-20). The lysate was centrifuged at 4,000 g for 5 min and precleared with 20 ΞΌl of protein Gβ€“Sepharose (50% suspension) for 30 min at 4Β°C. The cell lysate (500 ΞΌl) was incubated with or without 3 ΞΌl of anti-Apg1 antiserum for 2.5 h at 4Β°C. Immunocomplexes were collected on protein Gβ€“Sepharose beads and washed three times with Tween lysis buffer. The resultant immunocomplexes were subjected to 7.5% SDS-PAGE and analyzed further by immunoblotting with anti-myc ascite (9E10) to detect myc-tagged Cvt9 or with anti-HA ascite (16B12) to detect HA-tagged Apg1. Coimmunoprecipitation of 3Γ—HA-Cvt9 and 3Γ—myc-Cvt9 was performed in essentially the same manner.
